Yeah, I can go.

01:01:53.480 --> 01:02:04.200
I think one of the fun things that I've experienced with like working here is that like even like when I'm like writing our docs, it's like some people have never interfaced with props before.

01:02:05.300 --> 01:02:08.980
And so reflex in a way is like a bridge to the web ecosystem.

01:02:09.680 --> 01:02:16.920
So it's been fun thinking about like what are the mental models that I can take in Python to help explain things that are in web?

01:02:17.500 --> 01:02:20.180
And it's like, how can you bring those in and then create pathways?

01:02:21.200 --> 01:02:25.780
There's not a lot of event-driven stuff in Python,

01:02:26.060 --> 01:02:27.660
but so much of the web is event-driven.

01:02:28.160 --> 01:02:29.340
It's callbacks and stuff, yeah.

01:02:30.880 --> 01:02:35.760
I guess for me, I think I'm just excited about thinking about new kind of user interfaces,

01:02:36.110 --> 01:02:39.720
both in terms of coding APIs and actual user interfaces

01:02:40.040 --> 01:02:41.780
that people are going to be able to build upcoming.

01:02:41.970 --> 01:02:45.440
I think the current web frameworks, the Django's and Flask,

01:02:45.600 --> 01:02:46.960
they've been around for a long time,

01:02:47.140 --> 01:02:48.260
And I think they have a lot of great stuff,

01:02:48.350 --> 01:02:49.560
but there's also a lot of new stuff

01:02:49.800 --> 01:02:52.640
that I think a next generation of web frameworks could add

01:02:54.539 --> 01:02:55.960
to accelerate a lot of work.

01:02:56.160 --> 01:02:58.460
And I'm just excited about thinking of what

01:02:58.530 --> 01:03:00.120
are those features, like how can we accelerate,

01:03:00.360 --> 01:03:01.760
while keeping the good stuff that's already

01:03:01.940 --> 01:03:03.320
been discovered before.

01:03:03.800 --> 01:03:05.560
And yeah, I think there's, especially now,

01:03:07.339 --> 01:03:08.780
like a lot more people are building,

01:03:08.870 --> 01:03:11.080
a lot more people are becoming builders and sharing.

01:03:11.320 --> 01:03:13.500
So I'm excited about empowering all those people.

01:03:13.640 --> 01:03:13.700
Yeah.

01:03:16.120 --> 01:03:36.480
There's a lot of obstructions to think through in terms of how can we create guarantees that can enable someone to be successful in the long term, especially when it comes to building apps that can serve hopefully millions of people and millions of traffic, but then also being flexible enough that they can still start easily.

01:03:38.580 --> 01:03:39.580
Yeah, that's a challenge.

01:03:41.680 --> 01:03:44.480
There's a lot of places that are struggling with those challenges

